<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2>Skill Development in Higher Education</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Today, there is a large chunk of the unemployed population consisting of highly educated youth who fail to find employment because of a lack of skills, and skilled individuals who lack eligibility because of a lack of knowledge.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>And, therefore, the need to provide skill-based learning in higher education to help students receive vocational training besides academics to improve their chances of better employment and a successful career.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Because of this need, vocational education is being considered as part of a structured program at the university level.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>This will provide multiple opportunities to students who will acquire skills related to particular professions along with general education.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>This will help students pursue graduation in a variety of vocations besides the mainstream subjects, such as science, arts, commerce, medicine, engineering, etc.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Students will get the freedom to select the vocation of their choice and make a career in it. Moreover, thanks to the skill development programs, students will get practical experiences in vocational training that will give them better chances at employability.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>‍</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2>Skill Development Program: How They Help the Youth?</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The government of India has several plans for skill development to improve employment opportunities for the youth.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>These programs not only provide the vocational training required to improve job prospects but also help develop personalities, enhance work proficiency, and improve communication skills, time management, and negotiation skills.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The skill development programs also help the youth identify their interests and talents. It helps them develop flexibility, reliability, productivity, and efficiency.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>All of this goes on to improve their chances of successful careers and widen their career opportunities.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>‍</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:heading -->
<h2>Skill Development in India</h2>
<!-- /wp:heading -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The government of India launched an initiative in the year 2015 called Skill India. It aimed to train 40 crore Indians in a variety of industrial jobs. Its goal: Empower the youth with schemes and training courses by the year 2022.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>The benefits of this initiative are:</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>● Better job opportunities, better-paying jobs, and a higher standard of living for the youth.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>● Development in every sector of the economy and every sector experiencing equal growth.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>● Trained individuals entering the workforce, which will lead to better and faster results and a boost to the Indian economy.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>Various courses are offered as part of this initiative, such as management and development programs, entrepreneurship development programs, skill development programs, promotion of small enterprises, cluster development, lending schemes, etc.</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->

<!-- wp:paragraph -->
<p>‍</p>
<!-- /wp:paragraph -->
